name: vectorized-shoreline-of-guam-derived-from-ikonos-satellite-imagery-2000-through-2003
notes: IKONOS imagery was purchased to support the Pacific Islands Geographic Information System (GIS) project and the National Ocean Service's (NOS) coral mapping activities. One-meter panchromatic and four-meter multispectral data were purchased for the Territory of Guam. A digital vector shoreline was manually digitized from the one-meter panchromatic imagery to provide accurate, up-to-date shoreline data for the region.
